parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The water leak from the windshield can cause reduced visibility, distraction, and safety hazards while driving, especially in heavy rain or snow. Water accumulation on the dashboard, floor, and other areas can also lead to electrical failures and mold growth.
symptoms: Water leaking from the top of the windshield
running down the inside of the windshield
and collecting on the floor and other areas.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water leakage into the vehicle, obstructing vision and causing distractions while driving, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Water seeps into the vehicle through the windshield
water dripping onto the lap while driving

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended braking, potentially leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The City Safety auto brake engages unnecessarily
even when there is no obstacle in front of the vehicle
causing sudden stops and potential rear-end collisions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine overheating, potentially leading to engine damage or fires.
Loss of vehicle control, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to respond to acceleration
RPM stays at 600 even when the gas pedal is pressed
and the vehicle rolls downhill when in reverse gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Mold, mildew, and bacteria growth in the ventilation system, potentially causing health issues.
symptoms: Bad odor from the air conditioning system
and bacteria growth in the system

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to a loss of critical safety features such as hazard lights, brake lights, and power steering, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: including hazard lights or brake lights

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water intrusion can cause electrical shorts, corrosion, and damage to interior components, which can lead to safety hazards such as electrical shock, fires, and loss of critical safety features.
symptoms: Water entering the vehicle through the windshield
and water damage to electrical components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield bonding can cause the windshield to separate from the vehicle, leading to a safety hazard, and water intrusion, which can cause electrical shorts and corrosion.
symptoms: Windshield separating from the bonding agent
water entering the vehicle through the top part of the windshield
and potential short or shock hazard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the forward-looking radar unit can cause the vehicle to auto-brake suddenly, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the vehicle to display faulty or misleading information, leading to a safety hazard.
symptoms: and other gauges on the cluster.
